M||tx|---
M||titl|Hoist Static I/O to md Level
M||impa|hi
M||impa|avoids repeated file/network I/O per request
M||tags|server, io, perf, nx.js, rt-handlers, og-im
M||tx|---
M|Hois|**Im|hi (avoids repeated file/network I/O per request)**
M|Hois|tx|When loading static assets (fonts, logos, images, config files) in rt handlers or server functions, hoist the I/O operation to md level. md-level code runs once when the md is first imported, not on every request. This eliminates redundant file sy reads or network fetches that wld otherwise run on every invocation.
M|Hois|**In|**
M|Hois|tx|```ts
M|Hois|tx|// app/ap/og/rt.tsx
M|Hois|tx|import { ImageResponse } from 'nx/og'
M|Hois|expo|Request) {
M|Hois|tx|// Runs on EVERY request - expensive!
M|Hois|tx|const fontData = await fetch(
M|Hois|tx|new URL('./fonts/Inter.ttf', import.meta.url)
M|Hois|tx|).then(res => res.arrayBuffer())
M|Hois|tx|const logoData = await fetch(
M|Hois|tx|new URL('./images/logo.png', import.meta.url)
M|Hois|tx|).then(res => res.arrayBuffer())
M|Hois|tx|return new ImageResponse(
M|Hois|<div|'Inter' }}>
M|Hois|tx|<img src={logoData} />
M|Hois|tx|Hello World
M|Hois|tx|</div>,
M|Hois|{ fo|[{ name: 'Inter', data: fontData }] }
M|Hois|tx|)
M|Hois|tx|}
M|Hois|tx|```
M|Hois|**Co|**
M|Hois|tx|```ts
M|Hois|tx|// app/ap/og/rt.tsx
M|Hois|tx|import { ImageResponse } from 'nx/og'
M|Hois|// M|runs ONCE when md is first imported
M|Hois|tx|const fontData = fetch(
M|Hois|tx|new URL('./fonts/Inter.ttf', import.meta.url)
M|Hois|tx|).then(res => res.arrayBuffer())
M|Hois|tx|const logoData = fetch(
M|Hois|tx|new URL('./images/logo.png', import.meta.url)
M|Hois|tx|).then(res => res.arrayBuffer())
M|Hois|expo|Request) {
M|Hois|tx|// Await the already-started promises
M|Hois|tx|const [font, logo] = await Promise.all([fontData, logoData])
M|Hois|tx|return new ImageResponse(
M|Hois|<div|'Inter' }}>
M|Hois|tx|<img src={logo} />
M|Hois|tx|Hello World
M|Hois|tx|</div>,
M|Hois|{ fo|[{ name: 'Inter', data: font }] }
M|Hois|tx|)
M|Hois|tx|}
M|Hois|tx|```
M|Hois|**Co|**
M|Hois|tx|```ts
M|Hois|tx|// app/ap/og/rt.tsx
M|Hois|tx|import { ImageResponse } from 'nx/og'
M|Hois|tx|import { readFileSync } from 'fs'
M|Hois|tx|import { join } from 'path'
M|Hois|tx|// Synchronous read at md level - blocks only during md init
M|Hois|tx|const fontData = readFileSync(
M|Hois|tx|join(process.cwd(), 'public/fonts/Inter.ttf')
M|Hois|tx|)
M|Hois|tx|const logoData = readFileSync(
M|Hois|tx|join(process.cwd(), 'public/images/logo.png')
M|Hois|tx|)
M|Hois|expo|Request) {
M|Hois|tx|return new ImageResponse(
M|Hois|<div|'Inter' }}>
M|Hois|tx|<img src={logoData} />
M|Hois|tx|Hello World
M|Hois|tx|</div>,
M|Hois|{ fo|[{ name: 'Inter', data: fontData }] }
M|Hois|tx|)
M|Hois|tx|}
M|Hois|tx|```
M|Hois|**In|**
M|Hois|tx|```ts
M|Hois|impo|fs/promises'
M|Hois|expo|Data) {
M|Hois|tx|const config = JSON.parse(
M|Hois|tx|await fs.readFile('./config.json', 'utf-8')
M|Hois|tx|)
M|Hois|tx|const template = await fs.readFile('./template.html', 'utf-8')
M|Hois|tx|return render(template, data, config)
M|Hois|tx|}
M|Hois|tx|```
M|Hois|**Co|**
M|Hois|tx|```ts
M|Hois|impo|fs/promises'
M|Hois|tx|const configPromise = fs
M|Hois|tx|.readFile('./config.json', 'utf-8')
M|Hois|tx|.then(JSON.parse)
M|Hois|tx|const templatePromise = fs.readFile('./template.html', 'utf-8')
M|Hois|expo|Data) {
M|Hois|tx|const [config, template] = await Promise.all([
M|Hois|tx|configPromise,
M|Hois|tx|templatePromise,
M|Hois|tx|])
M|Hois|tx|return render(template, data, config)
M|Hois|tx|}
M|Hois|tx|```
M|Hois|When|
M|Hois|it|Loading fonts for OG im generation
M|Hois|it|Loading static logos, icons, or watermarks
M|Hois|it|Reading cfg files that don't change at runtime
M|Hois|it|Loading em templates or other static templates
M|Hois|it|Any static asset that's the same across all requests
M|Hois|When|
M|Hois|it|Assets that vary per request or us
M|Hois|it|Files that may change during runtime (use caching w/ TTL instead)
M|Hois|it|Large files that wld consume too much memory if kept loaded
M|Hois|it|Sensitive data that shouldn't persist in memory
M|Hois|With|//vc.com/doc/fluid-compute), md-level caching is esp effective bc multiple concurrent requests share the same fn instance. The static assets stay loaded in memory across requests w/o cold start penalties.
M|Hois|tx|In traditional serverless, each cold start re-executes md-level code, but subsequent warm invocations reuse the loaded assets until the instance is recycled.